Your package lzop failed to build from source in current rawhide.
http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=12834094
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_24_Mass_Rebuild

This is already fixed in Suse:
https://build.opensuse.org/source/Archiving/lzop/lzop-1.03-gcc6.patch?rev=666fa50a520eb7651ee3f7c125b03e78
I can confirm the above patch fixes the bug...

This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase
Robert, have you had time to look at the patch referred in comment #4?

Kamil, I am very sorry, I didn't have a look to it. Unfortunately the URL you mentioned above requires some kind of authentication. I guess the URL https://build.opensuse.org/package/view_file/Archiving/lzop/lzop-1.03-gcc6.patch is the same patch. Applied that one to the package - thank you for your effort, the time and the reminder!
